        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 6:19PM CDT until June 8 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 619 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles southwest
of Dinosaur Valley State Park, or 14 miles east of Stephenville,
moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Iredell around 655 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Tolar,
Walnut Springs, Eulogy, Rainbow, Johnsville, Paluxy, Brazos Point,
Chalk Mountain, Duffau, and Morgan.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection stay inside a sturdy structure and keep away from
windows.</instruction>
